# EXAMPLE TEMPLATE - Copy and customize this to create your own EOD report templates
# This file is ignored by tab completion (ends with .example)
#
# METADATA FORMAT:
# TEMPLATE: <name>          - Human-readable template name
# SLUG: <slug>              - Short name for CLI usage (e.g., "eod 1 custom")
# DESCRIPTION: <desc>       - Brief description of what this template does
#
# AVAILABLE VARIABLES:
# {{DATE_LABEL}}            - "Today" or "Last N Days"
# {{REPORT_DATE}}           - Current date/time
# {{USER_EMAIL}}            - Your Atlassian user email
# {{JIRA_ISSUES}}           - Issues you updated recently
# {{JIRA_ISSUES_CREATED}}   - Issues you created recently
# {{JIRA_ISSUES_NEXT}}      - Top 3 assigned issues by priority & age
# {{CONFLUENCE_PAGES}}      - Pages you updated recently
# {{JIRA_COUNT}}            - Count of updated issues
# {{CONFLUENCE_COUNT}}      - Count of updated pages
#
# USAGE:
# 1. Copy this file to a new name (without .example):
#    cp eod-report-template.txt.example eod-report-custom.txt
# 2. Edit metadata at top (TEMPLATE, SLUG, DESCRIPTION)
# 3. Customize the template content below
# 4. Use with: eod_report 1 custom
#    or: jira-helper eod 1 custom

# TEMPLATE: custom
# SLUG: custom
# DESCRIPTION: Example template showing all available variables
==========================================
End of Day Report - {{DATE_LABEL}}
Date: {{REPORT_DATE}}
User: {{USER_EMAIL}}
==========================================

ISSUES I UPDATED:
-----------------
{{JIRA_ISSUES}}

ISSUES I CREATED:
-----------------
{{JIRA_ISSUES_CREATED}}

MY NEXT PRIORITIES:
-------------------
{{JIRA_ISSUES_NEXT}}

CONFLUENCE PAGES UPDATED:
-------------------------
{{CONFLUENCE_PAGES}}

==========================================
Summary: {{JIRA_COUNT}} Jira issues, {{CONFLUENCE_COUNT}} Confluence pages
==========================================
